{
  "stem": "25114.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You want name the bases, or want the names of the places?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, this was--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went to a-- a village called Chrapieniewo.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know how to, uh-- you find-- C-H--- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] C-H-R-A-P-I-E-N-I-E-W-O.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think it's-- Chrapieniewo.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we stayed for a little while there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and also, made big fires in the forest, and we went to gather some food at night.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And slept around the fire.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One side would get very hot-- the other side would get frozen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Have to change around, to sit with this side to the fire and then this side to the fire.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's how we kept warm.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, all of a sudden, we had an attack, because some of the people didn't go into-- the safest place to survive was in the forest.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But some people tried to get them a little bit more comfortable, and they tried to sleep in trusted-- trusted people's houses around the forest.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In this case, it was the-- the-- the whole group of the Bielski family-- his wife, his sister-in-law, his sister-in-law's son-- a few-- a few.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Most of them, they didn't want to go to the forest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And his sister and her nephew, Christian, a beautiful boy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Used to sing so beautifully for us near the fire.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And somebody [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] alerted the police, and they ambushed and attacked in the thing, and they died.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was the first time that somebody from that triad got killed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we decided to leave this place.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Before I came to that triad, they had built zemlyankas for winter-- prepared.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A zemlyanka is a place under-- under the ground. 'Zemlya' means 'earth' or 'land.' Earth.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they dig sort of a-- what do you call it-- not a square, but a--",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
